reviews.title: Not great, but not bad either!
reviews.review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] We had Red Baron for dinner last night, and though it was very filling and super easy to make in the toaster oven, I wasn't a huge fan. The bottoms of the pizzas got burnt before the cheese on top could fully melt. The taste was alright, not my favorite at-home pizza, but still better than most! Still a very filing dinner!!

reviews.title: Pizza Bread
reviews.review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] I bought this product in hope of wanting some delicious Pizza bread. However I wish I would have received what I wished for. There were 2 slices of bread.I felt like the Bread itself wasn't the type that I would consider using for a Pizza. I felt like it was somewhat thick and crunchy than I really wanted it to be.I didn't care for the flavor to much. The Pizza sauce was mild and the only thing on the pizza that had flavor was the pepperoni. The cheese was on their with it being the correct amount. Overall, It was an average pizza but my palette felt like it was missing more with how the bread was as well as the overall flavor.
